dmca.title: [TP-C583309B] Trademark Infringement, Cease and Desist: Millenium-Trading
dmca.body:
To Whom It May Concern:

 

We are in receipt of you Trademark Complaint dated August 24, 2006. The
disputed material in the above-referenced complaint is the domain name,
not the content of the website. As an ISP, we are compelled by Federal
Law to disable access of website if it infringes copyright or trademark
rights of third parties. This is not the case since the website
www.Millenium-Trading.com <http://www.millenium-trading.com/>  neither
uses the Trademark "Millennium-Traders" on his website nor has
Millennium-Traders content display there. As the disputed material is
the domain name and it is not under our control, because it was not
registered with us. This issue should be resolved either by the
registrar of the domain name Millenium-Trading.com , which is Tucows, or
ICANN.

 
Legal Response Team

________________________________

From: Webmaster - Millennium-Traders
[mailto:webmaster@millennium-traders.com] 
Posted At: Friday, August 25, 2006 7:28 PM
Posted To: Copyright
Conversation: [TP-C583309B] Trademark Infringement, Cease and Desist:
Millenium-Trading
Subject: Re: [TP-C583309B] Trademark Infringement, Cease and Desist:
Millenium-Trading


THE NAME IS THE INFRINGMENT, NOT THE CONTENTS. COPY THE URL IN THE
ADDRESS WINDOW AND YOU WILL SEE THE PAGE LOADS.
 
THE NAME IS INFRINGEMENT ON MILLENNIUM-TRADERS.COM.

        ----- Original Message ----- 
        From: Copyright <mailto:Copyright@theplanet.com>  
        To: webmaster@millennium-traders.com 
        Cc: Theplanet@chillingeffects.org 
        Sent: Friday, August 25, 2006 5:34 PM
        Subject: FW: [TP-C583309B] Trademark Infringement, Cease and
Desist: Millenium-Trading

        We are unable to locate on the web page
www.Millenium-Trading.com/  any of the material that you claim is being
infringed as of 4:33:32 p.m. (GMT-6).

         

        Legal Response Team

        ThePlanet.com
